{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κληρονομ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>inherit</b>, with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, ὥσπερ τῆς οὐσίας, οὕτω καὶ τῆς φιλίας τῆς πατρικῆς κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.2, compare 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 4.7, 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 127; ὅς γ᾽ ἐκεκληρονομήκεις τῶν.. χρημάτων πλεῖν ἢ πέντε ταλάντων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.312; μὴ πλειόνων ἢ μιᾶς [κληρονομίας] τὸν αὐτὸν κ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1309a25: with _accusative_ _of things_, 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 88, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMort.” 11.3, “BGU” 19 ii 1 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.: <i>absolutely</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Morte - Papiri Ercolanesi” 24. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>acquire, obtain</b>, τὴν ἐπ᾽ ἀσεβείᾳ δόξαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.22.3; φήμην [prev. author] 18.55.8; θρόνον βασιλείας LXX.1Mac.2.57 \">LXX+2nd c.BC+</a>]; τὴν γῆν <b>receive possession of</b> the promised land, Palestine,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Lev.20.24, LXX.Deu.4.1 \">LXX</a>] (also, <b>obtain</b> all that God has promised,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Psa.36(37).11, cf. NT.Matt.5.5)\">LXX+NT</a>]; <b>obtain</b> salvation, ζωὴν αἰώνιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.19.29. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>to be an inheritor</b> or <b>heir</b>, τινος <b>of</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 20 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: more frequently τινα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC: Posidonius Historicus 36J., 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Sulla” 2, “PGnom.” 5, +others (2nd c.AD), “Anthologia Graeca” 11.202, etc.; κ. τινὰ τῆς οὐσίας 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 45.47: _metaphorically_, σῆτες καὶ σκώληκες -ομήσου